HEADWORD: Suspiral
<hw>Sus*pir"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Suspire</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A breathing hole; a vent or
ventiduct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A spring of water passing under ground toward a
cistern or conduit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suspiration</ent>⟦br⟧
